Alice had always believed that life was a quiet journey, but one day she found herself standing beneath a spotlight that refused to dim. The world around her had transformed into a stage, and every person she met seemed to be playing a role in a grand performance.
 At first, she was bewildered, unsure whether she was the audience or the star, but gradually she realized that the show was about her, and she had no choice but to participate. 
The curtain rose, and Alice stepped forward, discovering that behind the glamour of the stage lay hidden truths, whispered secrets, and a script she had never agreed to follow. 
As the acts unfolded, she began to question the difference between reality and illusion, wondering if freedom meant breaking away from the script or embracing it with courage. 
In the final act, Alice stood tall, no longer afraid of the spotlight, ready to decide whether she would continue the performance or write her own ending.


